  <title>Nonmetallic Mineral Locations</title>
  <abstract>&lt;DIV STYLE="text-align:Left;">&lt;DIV>&lt;DIV>&lt;P>&lt;SPAN>Geologists use the term 'Industrial Minerals' to describe nonmetallic minerals that have economic or industrial uses. Their characteristics and means of formation are highly variable. Examples of these minerals include garnet, fluorite, quartz, beryl, sulfur, gypsum, mica, and many others.&lt;/SPAN>&lt;/P>&lt;/DIV>&lt;/DIV>&lt;/DIV></abstract>
